snippet.title: Adley Niko & Navey doctor visit and Shots - family picnic with fish! more playing at pirate island!
snippet.description:
Halloween crafts and painting with the kids 🎃

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Doctor Day Ever 1154

Breakfast is the most important meal of the day. So when I decide to make pancakes, I use only the best ingredients...Aldey and Niko Bear!! This morning starts off with some dad vs kids running around the house, the kiddos trying to get away from me as use them to make pancakes. I crack Niko like an egg, pour flour from Adley, and cook both Adley and Niko shaped pancakes on the grill, which is actually a couch, but its good old family fun.

Once morning play time is over, we load up the purple tesla and head off to the doctor. Navey needs a check up to make sure she is still doing great without extra oxygen and Adley and Niko need to get shots. They are so brave. They didn't even cry!! After all the test and shots, it's off the beach of pirate island for a family picnic. While eating, we find that the fish in the lake are very interest in our chicken nuggets. Adley drops a piece in and it's quickly snatched up. I hold a piece just outside the water and the fish jumped up to get it from me. Jenny tries a science experiment and puts her shoe near the water. Sure enough, the fish thought it was food and go for it.

After lunch, it's time to play pirates and fairies with the kiddos. Fairy Adley has some flying dust that pirate dad and pirate Niko are tying to get. After tons of fun and running around at the lake, we head home for some arts and crafts, halloween gifts for the kiddos to unbox, and playing with new toys in the ultimate game room.

It’s so much fun to watch them and be able to pet them in this new design for a house!! It is so unique that we decide that this is a guinea pig SpaceStation. 

With our pets all settled, we show Scott our brand new game, a VR flying game that Adley is really good at. We do some family yoga, we all learn some new jumping tricks thanks to Adley and then we end this best day ever with shadow puppets!!

It's almost time to head back to the hotel, but first we get the kiddos the worlds biggest donut! (maybe not the worlds, but its HUGE!!)

Back at the hotel, we get ready to go swim and float in amazing swimming pools. But first, some Hide N Seek!!

snippet.title: This Indoor Skydiver Is Defying Gravity and Expectations
snippet.description:
Kyra Poh wanted to become an astronaut so she could fly. Then she discovered indoor skydiving (made possible with vertical wind tunnels). Today, she is one of the sport’s top competitors—flipping, spinning and performing stunts with grace and strength. The 17-year-old from Singapore has won more than 30 medals at indoor skydiving competitions all over the world and holds three Guinness World Records, including one for the most backwards somersaults performed in a wind tunnel in one minute⁠—68! Poh shows us why more girls, including her 9-year-old sister, are discovering the extreme sport.
